DAMATURU – Yobe State Governor Mai Mala Buni today approved the use of motorcycles in Yobe Northern and Southern part of the state. The Governor announced this during a sympathy visit to the palace of Emir of Nguru over the recent fire inferno that razed the market. He said that the residents are now free to ride motorcycles for their day to day affairs. This is part of his electioneering campaign to restore use of motorcycles when elected. Remembrance: Military Men Make Unquantifiable Sacrifices,… School Resumption: Oyo Govt Not Impressed With Low Turnout Yobe State earlier banned the use of motorcycles during the peak of Boko Haram insurgency.